"na tveva tappaccayā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upapajjeyya."
msgstr ""
"Because that might result in death or deadly pain. But when his body breaks "
"up, after death, it would not cause him to be reborn in a place of loss, a "
"bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "an7.72:16.4"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho so, bhikkhave, dussīlo pāpadhammo … pe … kasambujāto "
"khattiyamahāsālānaṃ vā brāhmaṇamahāsālānaṃ vā gahapatimahāsālānaṃ vā "
"saddhādeyyaṃ vihāraṃ paribhuñjati. Tañhi tassa, bhikkhave, hoti dīgharattaṃ "
"ahitāya dukkhāya kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upapajjati. (7)"
msgstr ""
"But when such an unethical man enjoys the use of dwellings given in faith by "
"well-to-do aristocrats or brahmins or householders, that brings him lasting "
"harm and suffering. When his body breaks up, after death, he’s reborn in a "
"place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.135"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an7.72:17.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

#. VAR: yesañca → yesaṃ (?)
#. VAR: cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ → … parikkhārānaṃ (s1-3, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an7.72:17.2"
msgid ""
"‘yesañca mayaṃ paribhuñjāma "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ tesaṃ te kārā "
"mahapphalā bhavissanti mahānisaṃsā, amhākañcevāyaṃ pabbajjā avañjhā "
"bhavissati saphalā saudrayā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Our use of robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the "
"sick shall be of great fruit and benefit for those who offered them. And our "
"going forth will not be wasted, but will be fruitful and fertile.’"

msgctxt "an7.72:17.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "That’s how you should train."

msgctxt "an7.72:17.4"
msgid "‘attatthaṃ vā, bhikkhave, sampassamānena alameva appamādena sampādetuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Considering your own good, mendicants, is quite enough for you to persist "
"with diligence."

msgctxt "an7.72:17.5"
msgid "paratthaṃ vā, bhikkhave, sampassamānena alameva appamādena sampādetuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"Considering the good of others is quite enough for you to persist with "
"diligence."

msgctxt "an7.72:17.6"
msgid ""
"ubhayatthaṃ vā, bhikkhave, sampassamānena alameva appamādena sampādetun’”ti."
msgstr ""
"Considering the good of both is quite enough for you to persist with "
"diligence.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
#. VAR: Idamavoca bhagavā → idamavoca bhagavā …pe… (mr)
msgctxt "an7.72:18.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

#. VAR: uggañchi → uggacchi (mr)
msgctxt "an7.72:18.2"
msgid ""
"Imasmiñca pana veyyākaraṇasmiṃ bhaññamāne saṭṭhimattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ uṇhaṃ "
"lohitaṃ mukhato uggañchi."
msgstr ""
"And while this discourse was being spoken, sixty monks spewed hot blood from "
"their mouths."

msgctxt "an7.72:18.3"
msgid "Saṭṭhimattā bhikkhū sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya hīnāyāvattiṃsu:"
msgstr ""
"Sixty mendicants rejected the training and returned to a lesser life, saying:"

msgctxt "an7.72:18.4"
msgid "“sudukkaraṃ bhagavā, sudukkaraṃ bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "‘It’s too hard, Blessed One! It’s just too hard!”"

msgctxt "an7.72:18.5"
msgid "Saṭṭhimattānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsūti."
msgstr "And sixty monks were freed from defilements by not grasping."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.72:18.6"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
